 the spirit of its particular time in a nutshell. The voices of this “polyphonic” reader are diverse: Briusov, Savinkov, Ivanov-Razumnik, Kollontai, Tsvetaeva, Shklovsky, Olesha, Zoshchenko, Zhdanov, Grossman, Evtushenko, and others. The range of specialists on Russian culture represented here is equally broad: Clark, Erlich, Grossman, Nilsson, Peace, Poznansky, Siniavskii, and others. Together they evoke and illuminate a complex and tragic era.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Russian & Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh1 aAkhmatova, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlok, Aleksandr, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBriusov, Valerii, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrown, Edward J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurgin, Diana L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurliuk, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClark, Katerina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCollins, Daniel E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDelaney Grossman, Joan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErlich, Victor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEvtushenko, Evgenii, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGor’kii, Maksim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrossman, Vasilii, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGroys, Boris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGumilev, Nikolai, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolmgren, Beth